Here’s my FULL guide to deliverability after $15M with email:

There are 976318 reasons why your emails could go to spam.

But there are only 4 levels that cause it:

   1. Server

   4. Content

If you have poor deliverability 1 (or more) is messed up.

Here's how to fix each one:

- Server -

Your server is the first (& most important) thing that can go wrong.

Every server has its own trust score affecting deliverability.

Every server has its own trust score affecting deliverability.

Generally people use 3 types of servers:

- Google
- Microsoft
- Private (AWS)

Google & Microsoft are highly trusted.

Use them both to be safe (also helps with provider matching)

But private servers (inframail, mailforge) have almost no trust and can get blacklisted easily.

Its hard to avoid their blacklists even if you know what you’re doing.

If you're new to cold email you should avoid private servers entirely.

- Domain -

Every domain carries around a permanent rDns record.

Bad domain locations (Namecheap, Cloudflare) lower rDns trust & increase the chance your domain gets blacklisted.

To be safe? Always buy your domains from GoDaddy.

To be safe? Always buy your domains from GoDaddy.

Aside from rDns you need:

- SPF record
- DRIM Record
- DMARC Record
(Use EasyDmarc)

If you find a domain is already on a blacklist:

  1) Stop sending emails
  2) Increase warming
  3) Wait 30 days

One last thing: NEVER send emails from your primary domain.

- Content -

Words like: "Free" "Guaranteed" "Money"

Seventy percent of business partnerships fail. And when they fail, it is ugly. 😱

The right partnership is incredible.❤️
The wrong partnership is painful.💔

I have a good friend who is highly committed to scaling his business. His partner is committed to sports cars, the beach, and travel.

To avoid a bad partnership, be on the look out for these SIX RED FLAGS:

🚩 Misaligned Values - Don’t wait until you are sharing an office to talk about values. A partnership is like a marriage. 💍 Before you say, “I do,” have a discussion. What are your financial goals? What kind of personal life do you want? What is your long-term vision?

🚩 Imbalance of effort - This is huge.

What kind of personal life do you want? What is your long-term vision?

🚩 Imbalance of effort - This is huge. ⚖️ If your partner isn’t giving as much as you — even if you just perceive it that way — things will go bad quickly.

🚩 Different locations - A partner in another city is a bad partner. If you are not under the same roof, it will be easy to suspect there is an imbalance of effort.

🚩 Lack of trust - You don’t need a sketchy partner, no matter how skilled they are. Someone you can’t trust will eventually screw you over. 💩

🚩 Different opinions - Business leaders have strong opinions.

Someone you can’t trust will eventually screw you over. 💩

🚩 Different opinions - Business leaders have strong opinions. If you and your partner can’t bet on the same page, it could blow up in your face. 🤯

🚩 Competing ventures - If you launch a side company, take your partner with you. If you don’t, you’ll have issues with imbalanced effort.

Only commit to a partner when there are Goldilocks conditions. If the conditions aren’t perfect, the partnership won’t be either.

⏳TAKE YOUR TIME. ⏳ Don’t rush. Wait until it is just right. Then crush it together.
